The evidence with the title 'Obama's numbers (january 2016 update) - FactCheck.org ' says Jan 12, 2016  ... Since president Barack Obama first took office : Homicides  ... There were 229,078 fewer violent crimes in the U.S. in 2014 than in 2008 , a drop of 16 percent , according to the FBI .  ... The number went down to less than 2.1 million in december , which is 614,000 fewer than when the president first took office . 
